  A Director of Litigation in the Adamawa State Ministry of Justice, Samuel Yaumande, has been kidnapped. A family source told SaharaReporters that Yaumande was abducted on Monday night at his residence in Sengere, a suburb of Yola, the state capital. He disclosed further that the kidnappers also seized a school principal and three others during the raid. Spokesperson for the police in Adamawa, DSP Suleiman Nguroje, confirmed the incident when contacted by our correspondent. 